summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Fourteenth Avenue, in the City of Seattle, from East Cherry Street to East Union Street, by constructing concrete walks thereon, with all necessary appurtenances, in accordance with Resolution No. 1534 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
